Arritmias ventriculares","guid":"KymxNjvfwXPIvOXfLXLe-g","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"108","text":"• Muerte súbita cardíaca","guid":"xVrkjTBSwpSIPgV27OJGPw","children":[]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"97","text":"4. Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"• Historia clínica: factores de riesgo coronario, consumo de alcohol, antecedentes familiares","guid":"Ie2Yx9DyDDh8XLzM-PV5jA","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"113","text":"• ECG: Hipertrofia VI, bloqueos de rama, ondas Q patológicas","guid":"JzEiZIAMTMWwc-_cdeTdjg","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"113","text":"• Eco: Dilatación biventricular, ↓ FEVI, insuficiencia mitral/tricuspídea","guid":"jhG514-Nc7JWfJ12Pc9H7Q","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"113","text":"• RMN: Realce tardío no transmural, fibrosis miocárdica","guid":"_zh2YpzHQ2mf4CYNLWqoTQ","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"113","text":"• Angiografía coronaria: Descartar enfermedad coronaria","guid":"SM1mmUdXa1zRGBycvtxpQQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"97","text":"5. Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"• Fármacos: IECA/ARA-II, BB, antagonistas aldosterona","guid":"kAFGywjACjTHXWFA8nJQcw","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"• Dispositivos: CDI, TRC","guid":"4wiXTh9zurdBt0E8D3sP3g","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"• Trasplante cardíaco en casos avanzados","guid":"kWI6GRFy7_wgIMRmp9K8Dg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"0","text":"Genética de la\\NMiocardiopatía Dilatada\\N(MCD)","guid":"XXbsTAuv8uRbdc1sbbx4Yw","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"1. MCD Idiopática","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"• ↳ Diagnóstico dado cuando no se encuentra causa específica tras evaluación exhaustiva.","guid":"UvjNg113LpkcnQf9pzqOBQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"123","text":"2. MCD\\NFamiliar","guid":"NEEUYTl-16sZayRREhlLUA","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"• ↳ Cribado clínico en familiares de 1er grado (ECG/Ecocardiograma)\\N→ Evidencia de MCD en 20-35% de los casos.","guid":"0OglxoHE1qXjvl1CDBI9OQ","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"• ↳ Establece el diagnóstico de MCD familiar.","guid":"3nSLw5A7aFJ_UkQZjozoiw","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"123","text":"3. Mutación de\\NTTN (Titina)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"• ↳ Proteína gigante (>35,000 aa) codificada por el gen TTN.","guid":"YP8ZybU8KClKsnUysBqVWw","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"• ↳ Variantes truncadas de TTN en 15-25% de casos familiares y\\N10-15% de casos no familiares.","guid":"TU-bQISTND7XXD3gxLW_4Q","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"• ↳ Variantes de truncamiento: sin sentido, desplazamiento del marco,\\No del sitio de escisión → Proteína truncada.","guid":"Rwq4D-VpphcoVmfnkYEMKg","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"• ↳ Localización de variantes en los transcritos cardiovasculares N2BA y N2B.","guid":"0trAGUohNjqEJJqbGeETgA","children":[]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"123","text":"4. Otras Mutaciones\\NGenéticas","guid":"AIGX36TarDISfAYzc_KKJg","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"• ↳ Sarcómero: MYH7, TNNT2, TNNI3, MYBPC3.","guid":"iOdy4K1BGeWKDmxQmeb8rg","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"• ↳ Citoesqueleto: Lamin A/C (LMNA).","guid":"_Vl3BsRUlX-qx9cqLbTLQQ","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"134","text":"• ↳ Canales iónicos: SCN5A.","guid":"TcaLlwNuH_fpLMbCZzSLPw","children":[]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"123","text":"5. Pruebas\\NGenéticas","guid":"6VfqbagTdxATUtayE1pyqg","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"• ↳ Importancia en pacientes con MCD familiar →\\NValoración del riesgo en familiares y manejo temprano.","guid":"yT1UawNY5FEDx2kPAlfGCg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"0","text":"Genética de la\\NMiocardiopatía Dilatada\\N(MCD)","guid":"W1yeyS7QHfFVh4fIv4ufxg","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"1. MCD Idiopática","guid":"","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"• ↳ En un % significativo de casos no se encuentra causa tras evaluación\\N→ Diagnóstico: MCD Idiopática.","guid":"rnyFiUAwH9uI9dC7VZxmzQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"143","parent":"140","text":"2. MCD Familiar","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"• ↳ Cribado clínico en familiares 1er grado (ECG, Eco)\\N→ Evidencia en 20-35% → Diagnóstico de MCD familiar.","guid":"1W7E5K-XzzH62yS6nmubhg","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"• ↳ Mutaciones genéticas en sarcómeros y proteínas estructurales.","guid":"YCSpXIg2Dmq6YDUhwvCUpQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"140","text":"3. Proteína Titina\\N(TTN)","guid":"Vj10rIYxYPeSBo3a3iX6yw","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"• ↳ TTN: Codifica la proteína más grande (>35,000 aa) → Ensamblaje sarcómero.","guid":"c-IqSo0UeRDa_rM2Rbbmcg","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"• ↳ Variantes truncadas de TTN en 15-25% de casos familiares de MCD y en 10-15% de casos no familiares.","guid":"m8MykYbUeTAN4Ii7s3BMVA","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"146","text":"• ↳ Tipos de variantes truncadas: Sin sentido, desplazamiento del marco, truncamiento en sitios de escisión.","guid":"_h15BQdrhsttrrZNmwTPbQ","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"146","text":"• ↳ TTN influye en transcritos cardiovasculares N2BA y N2B.","guid":"tu2Dh15xZPqVff73N-AL4g","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"140","text":"4. Implicaciones\\NClínicas","guid":"2tkUQkdTK_xqkohnQ9hkQg","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"• ↳ Pruebas genéticas necesarias en casos familiares → Identificación temprana, cribado en familiares.","guid":"5eeLP12wdgEcooltX5yeFA","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"• ↳ Riesgo compartido con miocardiopatía periparto (MCPP).","guid":"MXcRjhuFwLbEOIkWThn2VQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"0","text":"Genética de la Miocardiopatía\\NDilatada Familiar (MCD-F)","guid":"nCT6QqN9e6ghE4uND3ePFw","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"1. Localización subcelular\\Nde los genes:","guid":"mrLYhiS0tlsqzxBzwyTZaQ","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"• ↳ Clasificación según ontología genética.","guid":"PePmz3QGnX4l79PYeoYC7A","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"• ↳ Implicación en sarcómero, disco Z o citoesqueleto.","guid":"sflwaJY6LjkTnn0FOwdW_g","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"• ↳ 30+ genes identificados → Heterogeneidad del locus.","guid":"Mgx3sIlFjKuhdgQCy95pYw","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"154","text":"2. Heterogeneidad\\Nalélica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"• ↳ Múltiples mutaciones en un mismo gen.","guid":"3eKJ_M94DxIW4CmWj0jSNg","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"• ↳ Ejemplo: LMNA → Mutaciones causan MCD +\\Nalteraciones del sistema de conducción y arritmias.","guid":"d5paki43zv7PPWwN21IjAw","children":[]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"154","text":"3. Fenotipos\\Nsolapados:","guid":"8uIurFyjP5gjUVKhkSXbvg","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"• ↳ Genes sarcoméricos → MCD, Miocardiopatía Hipertrófica (MCH), Miocardiopatía Restrictiva (MCR)\\N→ Mismas mutaciones → Diferentes fenotipos en una misma familia.","guid":"nRXck81kYM06I0FC0Y2ZsQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"164","parent":"154","text":"4. Herencia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"165","parent":"164","text":"• ↳ Autosómica dominante (más frecuente).","guid":"bv27u8pABTvW6jVQnuOAcw","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"164","text":"• ↳ Autosómica recesiva → Familias consanguíneas.","guid":"kQw41ne2tlwCC-bP6brIPA","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"164","text":"• ↳ Ligada al X → Gen DMD.","guid":"Gy4t46zjB-bU3nDZK3hW7A","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"154","text":"5. Penetrancia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"• ↳ Dependiente de edad → MCD aparece en la 4ª-7ª década (rango amplio).","guid":"jviORUannRk5ri-LdN8eoQ","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"• ↳ Penetrancia incompleta → No todos los portadores manifiestan fenotipo.","guid":"F6ix-c-2bI3xMqD8x3L_zQ","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"168","text":"• ↳ Expresividad variable → Fenotipo clínico puede variar entre individuos con la misma mutación.","guid":"dvP0wim00Isc70INmXC_Kw","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"154","text":"6. Evaluación\\Ngenética familiar:","guid":"VKHRzeh0lbWCGfEuhKpYnQ","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"• ↳ Se recomienda consejo genético y cribado clínico en familiares de primer grado.","guid":"pNq3sm-i--6Y1l5sr0GdWg","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"172","text":"• ↳ Análisis genético en el paciente afectado → Identificación de mutación patogénica.","guid":"zeMFZ6Q-pRlRxloL3B98uw","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"172","text":"• ↳ Cribado genético de familiares en riesgo para vigilancia clínica temprana.","guid":"M-1cf4PVvSo6oozOoPtR3w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"0","text":"Miocardiopatía inducida\\Npor taquicardia (MIT)","guid":"RDSBXk0lfvmLC-L6Duzm-A","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"1. Definición:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"• Taquicardia prolongada → disfunción ventricular (diastólica y sistólica).","guid":"BL8hn0mmG4HiM02mm9MXMw","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"• Dx retrospectivo: corrección de la arritmia → mejora de función ventricular.","guid":"OE2-Ycr_DVvbQbY8sLJjIg","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"176","text":"2. Manifestación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"• Puede ser aislada o asociada a patología cardíaca preexistente.","guid":"1553395h6bI-K3OHKXBpRg","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"• Ej: Paciente con MCD leve + FA → tendencia a IC descompensada\\N(pérdida de función auricular + ritmo rápido e irregular).","guid":"LSycCzpdH4YSKKiA7YSKCg","children":[]}]},{"id":"183","parent":"176","text":"3. Etiologías a descartar:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"184","parent":"183","text":"• Hipertiroidismo (produce taquicardia y, ocasionalmente, MCD independiente).","guid":"UaxbiPDBT73FRZRovdyyzA","children":[]}]},{"id":"185","parent":"176","text":"4. Arritmias\\Ncausantes:","guid":"MxT6o_BiVjJW7_q-DyGqnQ","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"• Formas\\Npuras:","guid":"9qdw5tqJxbRxbebd0lJ9yg","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"• Taquicardia auricular incesante.","guid":"KNZRzCE8v5lCJSZwIF9kWQ","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"• Taquicardia de la unión recíproca permanente (niños/jóvenes).","guid":"3wzJEZsHWKhwl6pP_-s3kA","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"185","text":"• Otras\\Narritmias:","guid":"LmbQvdTqAj0Y7NldhGKo-w","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"• Extrasístoles ventriculares (EV) frecuentes.","guid":"NscZz6I5gPgEWs3lCVlH-Q","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"• Taquicardia ventricular no sostenida recurrente.","guid":"M8KfBsqprn7-tKcQHzDZRg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"176","text":"5. Diagnóstico\\Ndiferencial:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"• Confusión con taquicardia sinusal → ECG previo útil\\N(diferencias en morfología de onda P).","guid":"xfqQMMk58PUJ4EIUadd7xg","children":[]}]},{"id":"194","parent":"176","text":"6. Duración >\\NFrecuencia cardíaca:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"• Ej: MIT auricular\\Nincesante:","guid":"il-YG6OJEfTDWqko5OicrA","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"• Duración media síntomas ≈ 6 años.","guid":"aVQ3smRoPyv4XgvAslo4iw","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"195","text":"• Respuesta ventricular media ≈ 117 lpm.","guid":"e3hn5iow3KIsRt8tjDqYtw","children":[]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"194","text":"• Ablación → normalización de FEVI (casi todos los casos).","guid":"BALM1Tm9Ck4y0ZoQ5ukauQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"199","parent":"176","text":"7. Manejo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"200","parent":"199","text":"• Monitorización de 24h en FA para confirmar control de frecuencia (reposo + ejercicio).","guid":"fRJz30ajc1-W1gwVy_klYw","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"199","text":"• EV > 20.000 en 24h → Ablación mejora función ventricular.","guid":"zwu1e3o-Bzb4hxg6yuc_GQ","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"199","text":"• Mejora MIT: 3-6 meses tras corrección arritmia (ocasionalmente hasta 1 año).","guid":"_LhZkQ_hCT4nZXhYUvyrvw","children":[]}]},{"id":"203","parent":"176","text":"8. Disfunción\\Nresidual:","guid":"pX58JR_k4MuGrqiLHrpbXA","children":[{"id":"204","parent":"203","text":"• Leve dilatación VI post-normalización FEVI.","guid":"dKXLiGy0ieavtw4rD2P-bg","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"203","text":"• Recidiva arritmia → Deterioro función VI.","guid":"DFs7JTqri7kyv-tzTHQ3oA","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"203","text":"• Disfunción diastólica precede disfunción sistólica\\N(modelos animales/humanos).","guid":"oz-d6dowSq4X5xypLeHO-w","children":[]}]},{"id":"207","parent":"176","text":"9. Seguimiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"208","parent":"207","text":"• Comparar FEVI post-ritmo sinusal con reevaluación 3-6 meses.","guid":"FG-hNlyOfRffm_8Sy_dtuA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"209","parent":"0","text":"Miocardiopatía inducida\\Npor taquicardia (MIT)","guid":"V7ri12CJDOxBYLv6FcILtQ","children":[{"id":"210","parent":"209","text":"1. Definición:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"• Taquicardia prolongada → disfunción ventricular (diastólica + sistólica)\\Nsin otras patologías cardíacas evidentes.","guid":"nhWnOntVeKWmkqeyUteDsA","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"210","text":"• Dx retrospectivo: corrección de arritmia\\N→ mejora de función ventricular.","guid":"mzuhrzunq5A2ioMY8sNzwQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"213","parent":"209","text":"2. Manifestación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"• Puede ser aislada o asociada a patología cardíaca preexistente.","guid":"A_QVvA3rCZHem7smkRLsmg","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"213","text":"• Ej: Paciente con MCD leve + fibrilación auricular (FA) → tendencia a IC descompensada\\N(por pérdida de función auricular + ritmo rápido e irregular).","guid":"vFlNXAO-CixHrtUFiZUUpg","children":[]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"209","text":"3. Etiologías a descartar:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"• Hipertiroidismo (produce taquicardia + ocasionalmente MCD independiente).","guid":"HHp5th861PO_1OWEjqTJ3g","children":[]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"209","text":"4. Formas comunes:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"• Taquicardia auricular incesante.","guid":"CAxWYFxKkVFSyeVLSR4_iw","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"• Taquicardia de la unión recíproca permanente (en niños/jóvenes).","guid":"wVl4Ju4WYRozmst6EL0O9Q","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"218","text":"• Cualquier arritmia, incluidas extrasístoles ventriculares (EV) frecuentes\\No taquicardia ventricular no sostenida recurrente.","guid":"piyNa_javGKN5I0_C2w1IQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"222","parent":"209","text":"5. Diagnóstico\\Ndiferencial:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"• Confusión con taquicardia sinusal → Importancia de ECG previo\\N(detectar diferencias en morfología de onda P).","guid":"1OyAjcPPPyJaNBZChZrfhQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"224","parent":"209","text":"6. Factores\\Ncríticos:","guid":"TYIaVnMmG-AVkBdm6RFd7A","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"• Duración de arritmia > Frecuencia cardíaca.","guid":"tTK-bnZAgwIwfs5L9-Niig","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"224","text":"• Duración media de síntomas en MIT auricular incesante ≈ 6 años.","guid":"7Qi5oD4_cGNK3Y7smEFTrw","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"224","text":"• Respuesta ventricular media ≈ 117 lpm.","guid":"zXEIPwcvBGgHZgjpDyyx4A","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"224","text":"• Ablación → Normalización de la FEVI (casi todos los casos).","guid":"y4A6XITDOb-1fG5ig0Pgyw","children":[]}]},{"id":"229","parent":"209","text":"7. Manejo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"230","parent":"229","text":"• Monitorización 24h para control de frecuencia ventricular en FA.","guid":"Ch_uhH4TfKhGOA-D4MJXmA","children":[]},{"id":"231","parent":"229","text":"• EV: >20.000 EV/24h → Ablación mejora función ventricular.","guid":"GskC0HkrN43-UTmDL1PQKw","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"229","text":"• Mejora de MIT: 3-6 meses tras corrección de arritmia;\\Nocasionalmente mejora hasta después de 1 año.","guid":"JwbnLOadFktJV6xTBRl2tA","children":[]}]},{"id":"233","parent":"209","text":"8. Disfunción\\Nresidual:","guid":"26I9jCnF1KA6FotAkbsiZw","children":[{"id":"234","parent":"233","text":"• Leve dilatación del VI a pesar de normalización de FEVI.","guid":"Rl5ScCD-uhSuMkM4dGA2wQ","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"233","text":"• Recidiva de arritmia → Deterioro función VI.","guid":"For6M00vUvr69YnMH6rVEw","children":[]},{"id":"236","parent":"233","text":"• Disfunción diastólica (precede a disfunción sistólica en modelos animales y humanos).","guid":"CbHgavWEHtrGb4GGC5HZEA","children":[]}]},{"id":"237","parent":"209","text":"9. Evaluación y\\Nseguimiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"238","parent":"237","text":"• Comparar FEVI tras restauración de ritmo\\Nsinusal con revaluación a los 3-6 meses.","guid":"WcTR4L_lS0bcauElDs1dfQ","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":238,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Cardiología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Cardiología","filename":"Miocardiopatías","id":"map_312","resolved_references":[]}